HEADWORD: Puissance
<hw>Pu"is*sance</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. <ets>puissant</ets>.
See <er>Puissant</er>, and cf. <er>Potency</er>, <er>Potance</er>,
<er>Potence</er>.]</ety> <def>Power; strength; might; force;
potency.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ Youths of <xex>puissance</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The power and <qex>puissance</qex> of the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In Spenser, Shakespeare, and Milton,
<xex>puissance</xex> and <xex>puissant</xex> are usually
dissyllables.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

